=== TASK ===
# Loading / Success (Generic)

## Overview
Create a reusable, generic transient page (overlay, modal, or full-page screen) to indicate processing (loading) or successful completion of an operation across the Roam Resort platform. This component should be highly adaptable for various flows (inquiry submission, image upload, payment request, data export, etc.) and seamlessly integrate with the app’s design system. It must be resilient to runtime variability, accessible, and capable of automatic layout adjustments based on content length and viewport.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A generic transient UI surface that presents either a loading state (spinner/progress) or a success state (checkmark with optional confirmation message and action). It can render as a full-screen overlay, a centered modal, or a full-width section depending on context.

Goals:
- Provide clear, immediate feedback that an operation is in progress or successfully completed.
- Allow optional secondary actions (e.g., “View details,” “Continue,” “Go to Dashboard”) and primary CTAs (e.g., “Back to destination,” “Done”).
- Maintain visual consistency with the Roam Resort design system: luxury editorial aesthetics, calm navy backgrounds, warm beige content areas, bronze-gold accents, and refined typography.
- Ensure accessibility: high-contrast text, keyboard navigable, screen-reader friendly, and appropriate ARIA roles.
- Be robust against various data shapes and loading times; never crash if data is missing or delayed.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Spinner/Progress indicator for loading.
  - Centered spinner with optional inline progress bar or circular progress indicator.
  - Accessible, with aria-label and live region updates for screen readers.
- Success checkmark for completion.
  - Large, prominent check icon (bronze-gold accent) with subtle animation (fade/scale) on mount.
- Message text.
  - Optional headline (e.g., “Request submitted,” “Processing your stay inquiry…”).
  - Optional subtext or detail line for context (e.g., “We’ve received your inquiry and will respond within 24–48 hours.”).
- CTA(s).
  - Primary CTA: prominent bronze-gold button (rounded corners) for the next logical action.
  - Optional secondary CTAs: soft-beige with bronze outline or subtle text links.
- Layout behavior:
  - Centered layout for hero sections and CTAs.
  - If full-page, content is vertically and horizontally centered with ample padding.
  - If overlay, content is presented with a dimmed backdrop and clear focus trap when active.
- Visual guidance:
  - Use the brand’s color palette and typography; ensure legibility on both light and dark variants.
  - Subtle elevation via soft shadow and gentle transitions on state changes.
- Animations:
  - Smooth entrance (fade/scale) and exit transitions.
  - Hover effects for CTAs in overlay states; no distracting micro-interactions that degrade clarity.

Connected features and API integrations:
- This is a standalone transient surface; it does not call APIs itself but may display data returned from other flows (e.g., confirmation IDs, timestamps). It should gracefully handle null/undefined data and default safely using data ?? [] patterns where arrays are involved.
- If used in flows with data, ensure that no array methods are invoked on potentially null values (guard with (items ?? []) or Array.isArray checks).
- The component should not depend on a specific API shape; accept props for title, messages, status, and actions, with sane defaults.

## Components to Build
- GenericLoadingSuccessPanel
  - Props:
    - status: "loading" | "success"
    - title?: string
    - subtitle?: string
    - primaryAction?: { label: string; onClick: () => void; ariaLabel?: string }
    - secondaryActions?: Array<{ label: string; onClick: () => void; variant?: "text" | "outline" | "soft" }>
    - allowBackdropClose?: boolean
    - image?: ReactNode | string (optional decorative image)
    - dataPayload?: any (optional contextual data; must be handled safely)
  - Behavior:
    - Renders a full-screen overlay or centered card depending on context.
    - Accessible roles: role="status" for loading, role="alert" for success if appropriate, or aria-live regions for updates.
    - Guard all data accesses: treat dataPayload cautiously; do not assume arrays.
  - Visuals:
    - Loading: spinner with optional progress bar; message “Loading…” or custom title.
    - Success: large checkmark, success message, optional details, a suggested next-step CTA.
  - Interactions:
    - Focus trap when overlay is active (if modal behavior is chosen).
    - Keyboard shortcuts: Enter triggers primary action; Escape closes overlay if allowBackdropClose is true.
- Spinner
  - Accessible SVG-based loader with aria-label and visually hidden description for screen readers.
  - Configurable size and color to align with design system.
- CheckmarkGraphic
  - Scalable vector graphic with bronze-gold stroke/fill and subtle animation.
- TypographySystemAdapter (optional if your project centralizes typography)
  - Ensures headlines use Playfair Display (or similar) and body uses Inter/Lato, with provided weights and spacing.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks: React (TypeScript preferred), with hooks like useState/useEffect.
- State Management:
  - Use useState with array/object defaults as empty arrays/objects where applicable, e.g., const [items, setItems] = useState<MyType[]>([]).
  - If consuming data via fetch or Supabase, always guard: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Null safety:
  - All array operations guarded: (array ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(array) ? array.map(...) : [].
  - Access nested properties with optional chaining: obj?.prop?.nested.
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA roles, aria-live regions for dynamic status updates, proper labeling for CTAs.
  - High-contrast color choices and focus indicators for keyboard navigation.
- Styling:
  - Implement per the Visual Style section (colors, typography, spacing, cards, buttons, transitions).
  - Responsive behavior for mobile: overlay or centered card with proper tap targets.
- Reusability:
  - The component should be highly reusable across pages (inquiries, uploads, payments, exports).
  - Expose props to customize messages, CTAs, and visuals without requiring code changes.
- Testing:
  - Unit tests or storybook stories demonstrating loading and success states.
  - Tests include: rendering with only status, rendering with messages, clicking CTAs triggers handlers, accessibility checks.

### Backend
- No dedicated backend APIs are required for this prompt. Ensure the frontend can gracefully handle cases where loading data is absent or delayed and that it can accept dynamic content from upstream flows (e.g., inquiry submission confirmation IDs) without assuming shape.

### Integration
- The component should be pluggable into:
  - Inquiry submission flow (after form submit, show loading then success with next steps).
  - Payment link preparation (loading while generating link, then success with a “Open Stripe Link” CTA).
  - Data export (show loading while export runs, then success with “Download CSV” CTA).
- Props-driven integration: parent components pass status, messages, and actions, enabling universal reuse.
- Ensure consistent theming by using shared CSS variables or a ThemeProvider aligning with the design system.

## User Experience Flow
1. User initiates an action (e.g., submit inquiry, export data, upload file).
2. The app renders the Loading / Success (Generic) component in loading state.
3. If the operation completes successfully within a short time:
   - Switch to success state, show a confirmation title and optional details.
   - Present a primary CTA (e.g., “Continue” or “View Inquiries”) and optional secondary actions.
4. If the operation continues or delays beyond a threshold:
   - Update the loading indicator with progress (if available) or a helpful secondary message (e.g., “Still processing, this may take a moment”).
5. User triggers the primary or secondary actions to proceed.
6. Overlay or panel dismisses after the user action, returning to the previous context or navigating as directed.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:
  - Not required for this component specifically; ensure props are typed, and any dataPayload is optional with safe defaults.
- API Endpoints:
  - Not required; the component interfaces with upstream flows via props and callbacks.
- Security:
  - No authentication changes; ensure actions trigger callbacks that can be guarded by the parent context (e.g., only allow next steps if user is authenticated).
- Validation:
  - Validate that required props for status and primaryAction exist; guard optional actions to avoid runtime errors if callbacks are undefined.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Renders correctly in both loading and success states with appropriate visuals per the design system.
- [ ] All data accesses are null-safe: no direct access to possibly null values; use (array ?? []) or Array.isArray checks.
- [ ] Primary and secondary actions are clickable and trigger provided handlers; no crashes if handlers are undefined.
- [ ] Accessible: aria-labels, roles, and aria-live regions properly implemented; keyboard operable.
- [ ] Works as an overlay or centered panel across viewport sizes with responsive behavior.
- [ ] Styling adheres to the provided color palette, typography, spacing, and visual elements (cards, buttons, gradients, hover states).

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Maintain a modern luxury editorial aesthetic—clean, sophisticated, and immersive.
- Ensure clarity, calm, and high-touch feel in every interaction.
- Use atmospheric imagery or decorative background treatment sparingly to avoid visual clutter.
- Control motion with gentle transitions; avoid abrupt changes.

---

## Visual Style

### Color Palette
- Primary: Deep, muted navy (#23212A) for main backgrounds.
- Secondary: Warm sand beige (#ECE1D4) for content backgrounds.
- Accent: Rich bronze-gold (#A97C50) for buttons and highlights.
- Text: Soft white (#F8F6F3) for headings on dark backgrounds; deep charcoal (#3A3732) for body text on light.
- Details: Subtle gradients with sunset mauves (#B49587 to #23212A) and soft blush (#D1B7A1) for overlays or transitions.
- Combinations: Light beige on deep navy; bronze-gold buttons on light and dark; avoid pure black; prefer muted tones.

### Typography & Layout
- Font Family: Headlines with Playfair Display (or similar) and body/UI with Inter/Lato.
- Weight & Hierarchy: Bold/semibold for headlines and CTAs; regular/light for body.
- Alignment: Centered hero layouts and CTAs; left-aligned content elsewhere.
- Spacing: 40–80px vertical rhythm between sections; 24–32px internal padding in cards/blocks.
- Typography Treatments: Large airy headlines; uppercase section labels; subdued secondary text.

### Key Design Elements

#### Card Design
- Rounding: 8–12px.
- Borders: Thin, light/beige or translucent white.
- Hover: Slight scale-up and bronze-gold border glow.
- Hierarchy: Large image top, bold title, details/actions below.

#### Navigation
- Top nav: Transparent over hero; solid on scroll.
- Sidebar: Minimal; primary nav top-aligned; mobile expands to hamburger.
- Active State: Bronze-gold underline/highlight.
- Collapsible Elements: Smooth animations with chevrons.

#### Data Visualization
- Simple charts in bronze-gold/muted sand; navy axes/backgrounds; soft gradients; no harsh grids.

#### Interactive Elements
- Buttons: Bronze-gold fill (#A97C50), white or navy text; rounded corners; subtle shadow.
- Forms: Muted sand fields with clear focus ring in accent color.
- Hover/Micro-interactions: Subtle lift and glow; smooth modals/dropdowns.

### Design Philosophy
- Luxury editorial aesthetic: calm, refined, warm.
- Clarity and high-touch experience; minimal clutter.
- Visual storytelling with large imagery and refined typography.
- Serene, intuitive user experience; premium quality across all touchpoints.

